<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-197] Embedded consumer doesn&apos;t shut down if the server can&apos;t start</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-197</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If a broker embeds a consumer and the broker itself doesn&apos;t start (e.g., conflicting broker id in ZK), the embedded consumer is still running. In this case, we should probably shut down the embedded consumer too.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To do this, we need to either throw an exception or return an error in KafkaServer.startup and act accordingly in KafkaServerStartable.startup.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12530895">KAFKA-197</key>
            <summary>Embedded consumer doesn&apos;t shut down if the server can&apos;t start</summary>
